<m1><ue5><m0>U.S. officials plan<ql>
security, economy talks<ql>
<m1><ue5>  <m0>PORT-AU-PRINCE <m0>(--) Two top U.S. officials visit Haiti this week, in the midst of a deepening crisis of confidence in the country's future.<ep>
   John White, deputy secretary of defense, was expected Tuesday and Deputy Secretary of the Treasury Lawrence Summers is scheduled to arrive today.<ep>
   They will both meet President Rene Preval.<ep>
   ``White's visit will be centered on around security issues and Summers' around economic issues,'' U.S. Embassy spokesman Stan Schrager said.<ql>
